#. <html><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta content="Pali text from the Mahāsaṅgīti Tipiṭaka Buddhavasse 2500" name="description"><title></title></head><body><div id="text" lang="pli"><section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Bhūtagāmavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 17"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "17. Nikkaḍḍhanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on throwing out"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.44"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.17.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.250"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa428"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū aññataraṃ paccantimaṃ "
"mahāvihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonti—"
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of seventeen were repairing a large "
"dwelling nearby,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "“idha mayaṃ vassaṃ vasissāmā”ti."
msgstr "intending to stay there for the rainy season."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"Addasaṃsu kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū vihāraṃ "
"paṭisaṅkharonte."
msgstr "The monks from the group of six saw this"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Disvāna evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "“ime, āvuso, sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonti."
msgstr "“These monks from the group of seventeen are repairing a dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "Handa ne vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti."
msgstr "Let’s throw them out.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "But some of them said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.9"
msgid "“āgamethāvuso, yāva paṭisaṅkharonti; paṭisaṅkhate vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Let’s wait until they’ve finished repairing it.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa429"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six said to those from the group "
"of seventeen,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "“uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti."
msgstr "“Leave, we get this dwelling.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: paṭikacceva → paṭigacceva (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"“Nanu, āvuso, paṭikacceva ācikkhitabbaṃ, mayañcaññaṃ paṭisaṅkhareyyāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Shouldn’t you have told us beforehand? We would’ve repaired another one.”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, saṃghiko vihāro”ti?"
msgstr "“Doesn’t this dwelling belong to the Order?”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "“Āmāvuso, saṃghiko vihāro”ti."
msgstr "“Yes it does.”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.15"
msgid "“Uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, leave; we get this dwelling.”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "“Mahallako, āvuso, vihāro."
msgstr "“The dwelling is large."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.17"
msgid "Tumhepi vasatha, mayampi vasissāmā”ti."
msgstr "You can stay here and so can we.”"

#. </p><p><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.251"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.18"
msgid ""
"“Uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti kupitā anattamanā gīvāyaṃ gahetvā "
"nikkaḍḍhanti."
msgstr ""
"But they said, “Leave, we get this dwelling,” and they grabbed them by the "
"neck and threw them out in anger."

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Te nikkaḍḍhīyamānā rodanti."
msgstr "The monks from the group of seventeen cried."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?"
msgstr "When other monks asked them why,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.21"
msgid ""
"“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā amhe saṃghikā vihārā "
"nikkaḍḍhantī”ti."
msgstr "they told them what had happened."

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.23"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.24"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṃghikā vihārā "
"nikkaḍḍhissantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six angrily throw other monks out of a "
"dwelling belonging to the Order?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa430"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.25"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master.…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.26"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṃghikā vihārā "
"nikkaḍḍhathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.27"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.28"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.29"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṃghikā vihārā "
"nikkaḍḍhissatha?"
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you angrily throw other monks out of a dwelling "
"belonging to the Order?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.30"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.31"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.31a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa431"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.32"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ kupito anattamano saṃghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍheyya vā "
"nikkaḍḍhāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk, in anger, throws another monk out of a dwelling belonging to the "
"Order, or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs1.33"
msgid "(<em>17</em>:<strong>66</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.17.2"></a>
#. <a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.17.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa432"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.45"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa433"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunti"
msgstr "Another monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ."
msgstr "a different monk."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa434"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Kupito anattamanoti"
msgstr "In anger:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto."
msgstr "discontent, having hatred, hostile."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa435"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Saṃghiko nāma"
msgstr "A dwelling belonging to the Order:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "vihāro saṃghassa dinno hoti pariccatto."
msgstr "given to the Order, given up to the Order."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
#. <a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa436"></a><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Nikkaḍḍheyyāti"
msgstr "Throws out:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.252"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "gabbhe gahetvā pamukhaṃ nikkaḍḍhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"if he takes hold of him in a room and throws him into the entrance area, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Pamukhe gahetvā bahi nikkaḍḍhati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he takes hold of him in the entrance area and throws him outside, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Ekena payogena bahukepi dvāre atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"Even if he makes him go through many doors with a single effort, he commits "
"one offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa437"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Nikkaḍḍhāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets […] thrown out:"

#. </span><span class="gloss">
#. VAR: pācittiyassa → dukkaṭassa (pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukepi dvāre atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he only asks once, then even if the other makes him go through many "
"doors, he commits one offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.17.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa438"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid ""
"Saṃghike saṃghikasaññī kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it belongs to the Order, and he perceives it as belonging to the Order, "
"and in anger he throws him out or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense "
"entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid ""
"Saṃghike vematiko kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti "
"pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it belongs to the Order, but he is unsure if it does, and in anger he "
"throws him out or gets him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid ""
"Saṃghike puggalikasaññī kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, "
"āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it belongs to the Order, but he perceives it as belonging to an "
"individual, and in anger he throws him out or gets him thrown out, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa439"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he throws out one of his requisites, or he gets it thrown out, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Vihārassa upacārā vā upaṭṭhānasālāya vā maṇḍapā vā rukkhamūlā vā ajjhokāsā "
"vā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he throws him out or gets him thrown out from the vicinity of a dwelling, "
"from an assembly-hall, from under a roof-cover, from the foot of a tree, or "
"from a space out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he throws out one of his requisites from any of these places, or he gets "
"it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid ""
"Anupasampannaṃ vihārā vā vihārassa upacārā vā upaṭṭhānasālāya vā maṇḍapā vā "
"rukkhamūlā vā ajjhokāsā vā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti "
"dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he throws out one who is not fully ordained, or gets them thrown out, "
"from a dwelling, from the vicinity of a dwelling, from an assembly-hall, "
"from under a roof-cover, from the foot of a tree, or from a space out in the "
"open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he throws out one of his requisites from any of these places, or gets it "
"thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa440"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "Puggalike saṃghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the "
"Order, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure if it does, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.253"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid "Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as belonging to an "
"individual, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid "Attano puggalike anāpatti."
msgstr "If it belongs to himself, there is no offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.17.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa441"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "alajjiṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is shameless;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr ""
"if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "ummattakaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr "if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr ""
"if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid ""
"bhaṇḍanakārakaṃ kalahakārakaṃ vivādakārakaṃ bhassakārakaṃ saṃghe "
"adhikaraṇakārakaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr ""
"if he throws out, or gets thrown out, one who is quarrelsome and "
"disputatious, who creates legal issues in the Order;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr ""
"if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid ""
"antevāsikaṃ vā saddhivihārikaṃ vā na sammā vattantaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā "
"nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr ""
"if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a pupil or student who is not acting "
"appropriately;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.9"
msgid "tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,"
msgstr ""
"if he throws out, or gets thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.10"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.11"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa442"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc17:pts-cs2.3.12"
msgid "Nikkaḍḍhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on throwing out, is finished."

